metadata.name: Mina #68
metadata.description:
A generative series of a-symmetric compositions.

Mina is a search for new textures created by combining 3 colors with 3 different mathematical equations.

Observe how Mina blends and creates its textures in time.

Probabilities;

- 18 color palettes.

- 2 background colors.

- 4 line placements.

- 14 different compositions, most of them have variations.


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, December 2021
@distcollective

metadata.name: Steps of Yu - 禹步 (Yubu) #94
metadata.description:
In Chinese mythology, Yu is known as the one who regulated the waters after the great flood, a fact he accomplished by walking through the world. The flood may be equated with primordial chaos or, in a more synchronic mode of thought, the chaos underlying the existing state of order. And the cosmic order established by Yu may be identified with the societal order instituted by the emperor in accordance with the patterns of the universe.

In this generative piece of work there are many, many chaotic and random elements at play that are brought into a state of order, resulting in intriguing and storytelling compositions similar to traditional Chinese panel-based paintings and early Japanese Manga. It is as if each panel shows a detail from a snapshot in time from the many years of effort and adventures Yu experienced battling the elements on behalf of humankind.

If you'd like to find out more about this work, visit:
http://nor44.com/steps-of-yu.html

metadata.name: Returns #107
metadata.description:
Returns is an offline-first PWA and an interactive SVG. It combines the joy of interaction, digital color and minimalist sculpture with the potential of a long running, continuously unique visual. Based on “Shipping” from 2016, it is inspired by Anne Truitt, Ugo Rondinone, Imi Knoebel, Kelly Ellsworth and many others.

A subdivision slices the viewport influenced by width, height and depth. Corners are cut by replacing them with two new points, pulled towards each other along the edges. Shapes are “rounded" by repeating this step, keeping the new points close together. As colors change, so do the relations between shapes, even if geometry changes at a slower pace. New compositions are created on click or after a timeout. This progress over time allows for infinite iterations within the space of each token. It is the promise of a seeded starting point, plus the potential for unlimited new and unique iterations and states over time.

metadata.name: Sedimentary Dissolution #203
metadata.description:
This piece is inspired by the geological processes related to sedimentary dissolution. Dissolution is a form of weathering which contributes to the creation of new rocks. In this piece, various algorithms take on the role of dissolution, producing visual recombinations of the original "sedimentary rock".

Instructions ::

p : save a hi-res image
e : toggle erosion on and off
s : toggle structure on and off
a : toggle all effects on and off

If offset, rgb dissolution or cross-bedding is true you can toggle it on and off.
If these features are false pressing the key will have no effect.

o : toggle offset on and off
r : toggle rgb dissolution on and off
c : toggle cross-bedding on and off

There are 20 versions you can explore, all using the same features.
Use the left and right arrow to change the random seed. 
Pressing space will re-instantiate the original random seed.

metadata.name: Euphonic #826
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.
